      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in all model input parameters must be characterized and propagated through the model to quantify their contribution to output uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed on geometric tolerances only; blood viscosity, power-law hemolysis coefficients, and inlet velocity profile uncertainty not propagated. Flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
